1. Requirements
 - postgresql (even for compiling)
 - ocaml
 - ocamlduce
 - ocsigen and eliom with compiled ocamlduce support
 - pgocaml with lwt support
 - ocamlpam (recommended)

2. Run 

sh configure <toto>

   where <toto> is the user who will run the Ocsigen process. 
   We suppose for now that the postgresql user will have the same name.

   If you do not have ocamlpam installed, set PAM to NO in Makefile.config

   Then do

make sql

3. Create a postgresql user with that name (here ocsigen) 
and a database called ocsimore
(replace "ocsigen" by the name of your user):

sudo su postgres -c "createuser ocsigen"
sudo su postgres -c "createdb -O ocsigen ocsimore"
sudo -u ocsigen psql -f createdb.sql ocsimore
sudo -u ocsigen psql -f user_createdb.sql ocsimore
sudo -u ocsigen psql -f forum_createdb.sql ocsimore
sudo -u ocsigen psql -f wiki_createdb.sql ocsimore

If something goes wrong, you can delete the database by typing:
sudo su postgres -c "dropdb ocsimore"

4. Install pgocaml with lwt support (lwt branch of cvs)
http://merjis.com/developers/pgocaml

5. Compile ocsimore
make depend
make

6. Write and compile your site
or use example.ml:
make example.cmo

7. Adapt your ocsigen.conf using ocsigen.conf.example
and run Ocsigen with user ocsigen


